title: Government spending for SNAP benefits ( Food Stamps ) in the U.S. 1995 to 2020
summary: The chart at hand is a line chart where the x axis denotes Year and a y axis denotes Spending in billion U.S. dollars. In total the number of data points it has is 6.
In general Spending in billion U.S. dollars has rose over the Year.
Spending in billion U.S. dollars is slightly increasing from 1995 to 2010, and lastly roughly constant from 2010 to 2020.
The most drastic increase took place within the Year 2005 and 2010.
Maximum Spending in billion U.S. dollars, about 80.0 was reported at Year 2015
The lowest Spending in billion U.S. dollars, of value 18.0 was reported at Year 2000
